  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN184.1-kilavi">talaimakaṉ viṉaivayiṟ <app><lem>pirintu vantu eytiya</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3">pirinteytiya</rdg></app> viṭattut tōḻi pullumakiḻvuraittatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said in the delight of [their] embracing when HE, who had come [back] after parting for work, reached [HER].</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN184.1">
        <l>kaṭavuṭ kaṟpoṭu kuṭikkuviḷak kākiya</l>
        <l>putalvaṟ payanta pukaḻmiku ciṟappi</l>
        <l>ṉaṉṉa rāṭṭik kaṉ<supplied>ṟi</supplied>yu meṉakku</l>
        <l>miṉitā kiṉṟāṟ ciṟakkaniṉ ṉāyu</l>
        <l>ḷaruntoḻiṉ muṭitta cemma luḷḷamoṭu</l>
        <l>curumpimir malara kāṉam piṉpaṭa</l>
        <l>veṇpiṭa vaviḻnta vīkamaḻ puṟaviṟ</l>
        <l>kuṇṭaik kōṭṭa kuṟumuṭ kaḷḷip</l>
        <l>puṉṟalai putaitta koḻuṅkoṭi mullai</l>
        <l>yārkaḻal putuppū vuyirppi ṉīkkit</l>
        <l>teḷḷaṟal parukiya tirumarup peḻiṟkalai</l>
        <l>puḷḷiyam piṇaiyoṭu vatiyu māṅkaṭ</l>
        <l>kōṭuṭai kaiyar tuḷareṟi viṉaina</l>
        <l>rariya lār<supplied>kai</supplied>yar viḷaimakiḻ tūṅkac</l>
        <l>celkatir maḻukiya vuruva ñāyiṟṟuc</l>
        <l>cekkar vāṉañ ceṉṟa poḻutiṟ</l>
        <l>kaṟpā laruviyi ṉolikku naṟṟērt</l>
        <l>tārmaṇi palavuṭa ṉiyampac</l>
        <l>cīrmiku ku<supplied>ri</supplied>ciṉī vantuniṉ ṟatuvē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Sweet it was indeed (4)</l>
        <l>not only to the good woman of much-praised excellence</l>
        <l>who has given birth to a son who has become a light</l>
        <l>to [this] home, with god[-like] fidelity, [but] also to me, (1-3)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">let your life span excel,</l>
        <l>– your coming [back and] standing [there], the excellent master, (19)</l>
        <l>while the bells rang, many together, on the garland (18)</l>
        <l>of [your] good chariot that sounded like a waterfall on the stones, (17)</l>
        <l>at a time when the redness had gone from the sky, (16)</l>
        <l>with the sun’s form dimmed in [its] declining beams, (15)</l>
        <l>while those working to throw up the weeds, hooks in hand, (13)</l>
        <l>linger with growing delight, becoming full of toddy, (14)</l>
        <l>in a place, where dwells with [its] dotted mate (12)</l>
        <l>the handsome stag with twisted horns that drank from the clear water, (11)</l>
        <l>parting with [its] breathing the new flowers with loosening stems (10)</l>
        <l>on the jasmine on rich creepers, which buried the low head (9)</l>
        <l>of the short-thorned Kaḷḷi with short(?) branches, (8)</l>
        <l>in the woodland fragrant with blossoms that opened on the white Piṭavu, (7)</l>
        <l>which came later(?) in the forest of flowers, buzzing with bees, (6)</l>
        <l>with an exalted mind that had completed a task difficult [to achieve]. (5)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
